{"author":{"id":"f9fa446e8ed3e658d3c614258df652e4a274cbe959879543932e114fa617de10"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1736634925,"nonce":"E/c+Qv6wrGtCVVsp9nNR3iqBECo=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDODBZtRc6l1JyJ","github-url":"https://github.com/dandi/dandi-cli/issues/1563","origin":"github"},"title":"Create custom domain for Read the Docs site","message":"## Issue description\n\nGiven the recent updates to the website routes (see https://github.com/dandi/dandi.github.io/issues/84) and particularly the renaming of the DANDI Handbook to `docs.dandiarchive.org`, as @yarikoptic points out it is confusing that we have a `dandi` RTD site for the DANDI Client.\n\n## Possible solution\n\nI propose that we create a custom domain for the RTD site and use `docs.dandiarchive.org/api/client` or `docs.dandiarchive.org/client`.  RTD allows for [custom domains](https://docs.readthedocs.io/en/stable/guides/custom-domains.html) but we will need to investigate further if we can use a custom domain that also includes a path (e.g. `/api/client`).  \n\nIf we agree on this being the solution, I would be happy to work on this.  I will just need the credentials for the `dandi` RTD account.","files":null}]}